    <body>
        <section><p>If <sourcexml>glp:note</sourcexml> is the child of <sourcexml>p/text</sourcexml>
                <i>and</i>
                <sourcexml>glp:note</sourcexml> contains more than one <sourcexml>p</sourcexml>
                child, then <sourcexml>glp:note</sourcexml> becomes a <targetxml>note</targetxml>
                that is a following-sibling of the <targetxml>p</targetxml> from which it originally
                descended. The children of <sourcexml>glp:note</sourcexml> should be handled as follows:<ul>
                    <li>Create <targetxml>bodytext</targetxml> inside
                        <targetxml>note</targetxml>.</li>
                    <li>Map the children of <sourcexml>glp:note</sourcexml> to children of
                            <targetxml>bodytext</targetxml>.</li>
                </ul></p></section>
        <example>
            <codeblock>
&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;pnum count="55"&gt;[55]&lt;/pnum&gt;
    &lt;refpt id="20010NZAR_360_p55" type="ext"/&gt;
    &lt;text&gt;
        To clarify, counsel for NZ Post and counsel for Mr Prebble if he wishes to engage counsel, should there be an appeal, only are to have access to the Business Case Report held by the Court. 
        &lt;glp:note&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/glp:note&gt;
    &lt;/text&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
      </codeblock>
            <b>becomes</b>
            <codeblock>
&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;ref:anchor id="_20010NZAR_360_p55" anchortype="global"/&gt;
    &lt;desig value="55"&gt;[55]&lt;/desig&gt;
